article.headline: E. Illinois 75, Tennessee Tech 58
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Romain Martin had a game-high 24 points and 11 rebounds to lead Eastern Illinois to a 75-58 win over Tennessee Tech on Thursday night. Edin Suljic added 14 points for Eastern Illinois (9-11, 6-4 Ohio Valley), which never trailed after pulling ahead 2-1 just under two minutes into the game. Eastern Illinois held Tennessee Tech (10-10, 4-6) leading scorer Daniel Northern, who averaged 11.7 points, to six free throws and 0-for-4 shooting from the field. Tennessee Tech shot 31 percent, and the Panthers outrebounded the Golden Eagles 44-39. Eastern Illinois led 33-20 at halftime. Kevin Murphy led Tennessee Tech with 11 points. The Golden Eagles beat Eastern Illinois 67-60 the last time the teams played in Tennessee on Jan. 5. The Panthers have won four straight games at home.
